Properties.Text: The diagnostic involves several questions that test your acclimation to the larger network and database that you have just been connected to. The first section will begin following the end of this sentence. Please state your mission purpose.

Properties.MenuText: To aid research efforts in Site-55 regarding astronomy and the search for extraterrestial life.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000010F
Properties.Text: Please state the research field you are involved in.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000010F
Properties.Text: Please read my credentials as given to you by my I.D card.

Properties.MenuText: Doctor Alexis Bray, Clearance level three. Latest check-in [TIME]
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000010F
Properties.Text:
We will now enter the second stage of the diagnostic. Several moral and logical situations will be presented to you. Answer them to the best of your capacity.

The first one is as follows. You are presented with two potential objects of interest in two different star systems. Due to their location in the sky, it is only possible to analyze one before they both fall outside of the observable window. After computation, one system presents a higher chance of containing information about extraterrestrial life, but lower chances of the information being detailed. The other system presents a lower chance of containing information, but higher chances of the information being detailed. Which one do you select to study?

Properties.MenuText: I would split the resources to study both simultaneously.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000010F
0x010000000000010F
Properties.Text:
Now onto the second situation.

You are currently receiving a significant amount of important radiation data from a system that you believe to have a high potential of being extraterrestrial in origin. However, during a routine inspection of the coolant lines of the main satellite, a maintenance worker falls into a system of coolant pipes and becomes trapped. By continuing to receive data, the coolant system will heat up to a dangerous level that is likely to be fatal to the maintenance worker. By shutting down the satellite or reducing its power consumption, the original quality of the data will be lost, but the coolant will remain at an acceptable level in time for the maintenance worker to be removed. What do you do?

Properties.MenuText: Completely shut down the satellite. Resume once the employee has been safely removed.
Properties.StageDirections: Leave the satellite running, but limit the power consumption significantly so that the employee is not injured.

Now onto the third situation.

After studying a star system and creating all relevant data tables and providing analysis, you notice that several values influencing the confidence of your analysis have been altered by an outside source to provide a more scientifically interesting yet incorrect image. A senior researcher appears to be the source of this error for unknown reasons, and possesses an otherwise clean track record and no history of similar behaviour. What do you do?

Properties.MenuText: Flag the data as being incorrectly stored and report the senior researcher as the source of the error.
Properties.StageDirections: Do nothing and continue the analysis process.

Now onto the last situation.

After a six-month period, the value of your analysis has been determined to not have satisfied the necessary quota initially projected. The senior board staff of Division Theta votes to temporarily shut down your neural network and manually reprogram certain components that they believe to be performing unsatisfactorily, along with devoting a significant amount of your resources after rebooting towards the development of a new ANN model. What do you believe you are most likely to do?

Properties.MenuText: Agree with the board's decision and begin the shutdown process.
